article.headline: Quinnipiac secures 91-87 victory over Iona

images.name: Iona Gaels vs. Quinnipiac Bobcats: Full Highlights
images.caption: Iona Gaels vs. Quinnipiac Bobcats: Full Highlights

article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. -- — Doug Young had 24 points in Quinnipiac's 91-87 victory against Iona on Sunday. Young was 9 of 12 shooting, including 2 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the foul line for the Bobcats (14-4, 6-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Amarri Tice scored 19 points while shooting 7 for 11 (2 for 4 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free-throw line, and added eight rebounds and three steals. Paul Otieno was 4-of—5 shooting and 7 of 8 from the free-throw line to finish with 15 points. Idan Tretout finished with 30 points and three steals for the Gaels (8-10, 3-4). Iona also got 15 points and two blocks from Wheza Panzo. In addition, Greg Gordon finished with 13 points and 10 rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
